  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity analysis was conducted on material property inputs and boundary condition assumptions to bound parametric uncertainty; results confirmed that construct stiffness QoI is insensitive (< 2% variation) to ±10% perturbations in cortical bone modulus and fixation torque. This UQ narrative is captured in the model risk documentation but is not separately linked as a structured SensitivityAnalysis node in this package.",
