      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions (linear elasticity, frictionless contact, rigid fixation blocks) must be justified by literature or sensitivity screening relative to observed experimental behavior.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) model form appropriate for sub-yield regime. Nonlinear geometric effects included (large displacement formulation). Frictional contact (mu=0.3) used for screw-rod interface based on manufacturer data. Model form justified by prior FDA FEA guidance and literature. Screening sensitivity on contact friction coefficient (mu 0.2–0.4) showed < 3% QoI variation."
    },
