      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must be directly relevant to the regulatory decision and clinically meaningful failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness predicts load sharing; yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm predicts post-yield structural reserve. All three QoIs are specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Relevance to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, screw loosening) established in literature."
