    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against required level 3, accepted given explicit COU scope restriction to static compression-bending loading. Quantitative validation metric E/uval < 1.96 satisfied for all three QoIs across two independent laboratories. Model risk level 3 with Medium assurance level is appropriate for a Class II device with Medium decision consequence and Medium model influence. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for predicting ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
